You mean the gaping hole that used to be the Pred cave?

--- In nbwrpg@egroups.com, "Moon Mist" <shadowwarrior_ax@h...> wrote:
> 
> * Rage growled as she sniffed the air, wondering just what that 
scent was.
> She had been following it all day, with her stomach growling in 
humger, 
> until she had come to this place.
> It wasn't anything that she hadn't seen before, just a hunk of rock 
with a 
> large hole in it, a cave and she knew that there had to be 
something to eat 
> in there.
> Yummy things always were in caves, they always thought it was safe 
there or 
> always took cover in one when it was raining.
> And she could smell something too, not sure if it was a yummy thing 
but sure 
> it was something.
> Rage looked at the enterance of the cave, not trying to hide 
herself or 
> anything as she stool less then 100 yards from the opening in the 
rock ( The 
> Pred Cave...aut she doesn't know that.)
> She didn't need to hide herself either, because if there was 
anything in 
> there to eat she could simply corner it and begin her feast.
> But for now she just waited, wondering what it was that was in 
there, and 
> her stomach growling in reminder of her hunger.
> Finally she couldn't wait anymore and began to move towards the 
cave, her 
> head down in in a stalking manner, but a causiouse one as well.*
>
